=== Etymology ===
From French ''hélicoptère'' which in turn comes from Greek ''heliko'' "helix, spiral" and ''pteron'' meaning "wing".

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:IPA|IPA]] (UK): /'heliˌkɒptə(r)/
*[[w:IPA|IPA]] (US): /'hεliˌkɔptəɻ/
*[[w:IPA|IPA]] (Australia): /ˈheliˌkoptə(r)/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]] (Australia): /'heliˌkopt@(r)/

=== Noun ===
'''helicopter'''

#An aircraft that is borne along by one or more sets of long rotating blades which allow it to hover, move or land and having a smaller set of blades on its tail that stabilize the aircraft.
#:''We flew over the city on a helicopter''.

